  <RulesElement name="Trap: Viper's Nest" type="Power" internal-id="ID_TIV_POWER_GUILD_WARS_1_171-1" source="Guild Wars" revision-date="3/7/2011 9:49:21 PM">
    <Category> ID_INTERNAL_CATEGORY_UTILITY,ID_INTERNAL_CATEGORY_DAILY,ID_INTERNAL_CATEGORY_DAILY_USAGE,ID_FMP_CLASS_6,ID_FMP_CATEGORY_14,ID_FMP_CATEGORY_36,ID_INTERNAL_CATEGORY_STANDARD_ACTION,2 </Category>
    <Flavor> A small vial of poison, a couple of sharp shards of wood or metal, string, a spring, and little luck... </Flavor>
    <specific name="Power Usage"> Daily </specific>
    <specific name="Display"> Rogue Utility 2 </specific>
    <specific name="Keywords"> Martial, Poison </specific>
    <specific name="Action Type"> Special </specific>
    <specific name="Attack Type"> Personal </specific>
    <specific name="Target"> Special </specific>
    <specific name="Effect"> You place a trap in an adjacent area to you. 
Standard Action: 1 unoccupied adjacent square to you.
Standard + Minor Action: 2x2 unoccupied adjacent squares to you.
The first enemy creature that steps into the square sets the trap off (Perception Check DC 17 + Rogue's Level to recognize the trap), taking 1d6 poison damage and ongoing 4 poison damage (save ends). All adjacent creatures take ongoing 4 poison damage until the end of their next turn.
Allies that move into the trapped area must treat the area as difficult terrain or they set the trap off. The trap lasts until its either set-off or disabled. </specific>
    <specific name="Disabling a Trap"> You can disable this trap (as a Minor Action) and reuse the power on a DC 15 (Dexterity modifier roll bonus), only if the trap has not been sprung and you are adjacent to it while disabling it. </specific>
    <specific name="Class"> ID_FMP_CLASS_6 </specific>
    <specific name="Level"> 2 </specific>
    <specific name="Power Type"> Utility </specific>
  </RulesElement>
